{"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"I think you can learn a lot by asking “why” in everyday conversations. I don’t think that most people think about the why of what they’re doing, what they like, or the things they choose.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You probably won’t get to any “truth” by asking why. You’ll learn more about the person than the problem, but that’s OK."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2016-04-14T07:22:28-05:00"}],"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/04-14-constantly-researching","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/04-14-constantly-researching"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"metadata":{"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"},"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}],"title":"Constantly Researching"},"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/brunow","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he."}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","title":"Brunow"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"All posts"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Archive","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentati